    "This aligns well with the 5WH questioning algorithm proposed by Wang and Zeng (2009).",
    "Chen et al. (2024a) used the similar 5W1H questioning approach with an example of \"flying car\" in their LLM effort to elicit product requirements.",
    "The final segment of the function, prompted by prompt 9, evaluates all the generated questions and filters out any duplicates.",
    "This is necessary because some generated questions may be redundant, and this step ensures that only unique questions are returned.",
